%N A284035 Upper twin primes which correspond to the hypotenuse in a Pythagorean triple whose small leg is also a prime.
%C A284035 A284034 gives the corresponding small leg primes in definition.
%F A284035 A284034(n)^2 + (a(n) - 1)^2 = a(n)^2, i.e., a(n) = (A284034(n)^2 + 1)/2.
%e A284035 The prime q = 3121 is in the sequence because q - 2 = 3119 is prime and {79, 3120, 3121} is a Pythagorean triple with prime small leg (see example in A284034).
%o A284035 (PARI) lista(nn) = forprime(p=3, nn, if (isprime(p) && isprime((p^2-3)/2) && isprime(q=(p^2+1)/2), print1(q, ", "))); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Apr 01 2017
